caption: Fun place to hang out!
Great place.  Good beer.  Good food.
Great food. Never had a bad tasting on anything I've tried here
When I went back in March before COVID hit it was one of the coolest places I've been in Baltimore. Free play was on, burgers were great and the beer was cold. Can't wait to go back.
Great place, great fun, great food, and most importantly great stuff wonderful place to go to and its really family oriented and you cant beat free arcade machines

Stumbled into north ave market on what seemed like a video game night. There were so many activities available. I got to play some madden on a ps2: serious nostalgia. They had some of my favorite local beers available. On top of all that there was a live Dj and beautiful lighting set up.
Very unique place with pretty good food. Prices a bit high but all the arcade games are free to play so I think that's a fair trade off

What a great spot to meet other gamers and hang out. My friends met here and happened to arrive on "free play" night where they set up consoles and had unlimited play on the arcade machines. It's a large space so there was plenty of games for everyone to play. Burger Time is my new favorite arcade game. There's a spot for coats and backpacks in the back. Bartender was really kind! Burger and fries were awesome. We sampled a bunch of hot sauces too, which was fun. This is the perfect place to play a variety of games with great people.
Great food n free arcade games.
Love the fries and wide array of sauces (look for them in the big refrigerated case). Arcade machines are in good shape and  feature true classics like moon patrol and tapper!
Great atmosphere. Decent burgers and fries. The homemade ketchup and hot sauce take the cake. The games are the star of the show. You will have a great time.
We had a fantastic time. The food and drink selection showed a lot of thought. The arcade games brought me back to my childhood.
Awesome food, even better sauce. Free arcade games and live music - what more could you ask for.
Pretty hip place.  The video game selection is limited for a “barcade.” They are going to have to really expand selection for this place to be legit
Great free games for kids and amazing truffle parmesan fries. Decent beer selection, good music videos and casual atmosphere.
Video games, great food, great drinks, crazy fun events. What more do you need for the perfect night?
Cool arcade experience with the family.

OMGGGG!!! Ended up at North Ave Market on a Thursday night after leaving an establishment in the area because it was too crowded. When I say I found a gem! The bartender Mike is AMAZEBALLS!!! And the burgers and fries are Bomb!!!! To top it off the music was so on point!!! I will be back!! In loving This place!❤️
Love the arcade vibe. Could use a roll away ping pong table? Bartender was great. See you again soon
Such a fun environment, lots of nostalgia with the video games, super friendly staff and delicious food!
Great place to bring kids. Good burgers. I wish they had draft beer.
Great burgers and fries. Good beer selection. Large space.
Love this place!
Great place and great arcade games and food :)

The atmosphere here is really cool and the fries were delicious. Service was pretty poor though, unnecessarily slow considering they only open beer cans and their signature cocktails are premade by bulk. Six bucks for a local can that I had to wait 15 minutes to order is a bit ridiculous.
Me and my husband enjoyed this place yesterday and the bartender/waiter corey was really nice.we will be returning to bring our 6 year old to enjoy the games. Mookie and cal
Awesome arcade machines that are free to play. Sometimes there's a cover but it's worth it.
Very cool place with lots of classic games!
For a bar that’s almost totally empty, you would think the service would be better. It took far too long to get the bartender to notice us and even longer to get 2 cans of beer.
Waste of money
Dope
Horrible customer service
Please fix NBA Jam.
Dope spot. Cool wines.
Seems like the guy working the bar was prejudice..

I saw the arcade sign from afar walking on the opposite side of N. Ave and made a note to come back. It’s Sunday and there’s some kids, some adults and some students. I have confirmed the games are Free! But there is also a solid diner style menu with staples such as burgers / vegan burgers/ milkshakes/ Disco fries and salads. There’s also Kombucha and cold brew, so you know it’s cool! There’s also a call out to “Secret Sauce co” which has sauce caddies at the bar, the tables and here and there with 5 or more types of homemade delicious sauces for your food. I scarfed down some fancy fries trying all the sauces. My favorite was billion island followed by carrot lime heat. 🥰 Apparently this location is set to expand. YAS!

Excellent food - burgers to hand cut fries. They even have a vegan selection. The vintage arcade games are free as long as you buy something from the menu.  Donkey Kong, Donkey Kong Junior, Donkey Kong 3, Frogger, burger Time, Pacman, Ms. Pacman and more. I had so much fun. They staff was so friendly.

The Secret Sauce Co. has a real winner here. Awesome venue with delicious burgers, fries, and a helluva selection of drinks. Plus, free play on classic coin-op machines and tons of consoles. Nice setup for Killer Queen as well.
Great fries. Free arcade games. Win win!
It was fun the games were free and cool the milk shakes and drinks were awesome but the food was just ok. Great concept but definitely need high quality food.
Honestly, what?! This place hit the vibe Perfectly. Food and cocktails off the hook and I cant get enough of that arcade pac man !! 😍😍😍
Delicious food, great music, the staff is the best!
The best smash burgers and fries on the planet, milkshakes and a free arcade. What more could you ask for?
Delicious food, great atmosphere, good music, and rad selection of old school arcade games! So happy to have this spot join the neighborhood!!!

They made a decent burger (patty was small though) honestly could have used more salt an pepper cause it tasted like flavorless meat BUT the fries were hot and crisp easily the best part of my whole meal an the shake was okay definitely not the best by far plus half the video games weren't operating properly. I would not go out of my way to come back would much rather go to five guys or even koopers tavern both are definitely better options
Exceptionally creative yet simplistic. Delicious.  Refined. Really gud stuff broh.

They have arcade machines  that are not free.  I walk in to play a game, pay my money, and the unfriendly bartender tells me “the games are for our customers!”. How am I not a customer if I just paid for the game?!  No other establishment would have an activity available to their customers for a fee and then tell them they are not a customer if they pay for it! Besides, if the guy had given me more than 30 seconds to finish my game I very well may  have ordered some food.  Really turned me off to what could have been a nice place!

Cute venue, with free arcade games (kid friendly). Good food with adult drinks. Pictured here is the Pinball Fries (w/ pesto and Parmesan) — it comes with bacon as well but I requested these without. The drink is called Virtual Reality (Tequila w/ Grapefruit, Aperol, and Lime).
Really cool new place! Very decent selection of food and drinks and lots of fun arcade style games that are free to play. There wait staff was very nice and well informed too.
Killer Queen! Indie arcade is great. Oh and that ketchup... :)
Excellent burgers, shakes, and fries!
Nice menu. Friendly staff. Did I mention the games!
Friendly staff, fun games, great music, and delicious drinks!

Free arcade games + natural wines and other great local beverages. Super diverse crowd and very welcoming atmosphere. A nice evolution of what Red Emma's brought to this corner. Fries were great. Seems perfect for groups.
This place is wonderful. Chill atmosphere and great games. Also the burgers are solid.
Super awesome place, great music, games are free, killer queen console, vegan burgers and kombucha are nice.
